

At least 21 Hindu pilgrims were killed and several injured when a truck and a tractor collided head-on in the central Indian district of Basti, the United News of India said Tuesday.

Ten women and six children were among those killed in Monday night's collision, it said, adding that 17 of the victims, who were travelling on the tractor trailer, died instantly.

The pilgrims were heading to the holy Hindu town of Ayodhya to attend a religious ceremony.

